<p class="drop-cap">The southern headquarters of Swaminarayan Sampraday, Vadtal is a small town in Kheda district of Gujarat, India. The traditional architecture depicting rich Indian culture in the carvings done in and around the temple. The temples contain three main shrines, where the central shrine honors Lakshminarayan Dev. Left to the central shrine honors Radha Krishna Dev along with Supreme Lord Swaminarayan in form of Harikrushna Maharaj. In the right most shrine, honors Vasudev, Dharamdev &amp; Bhaktimata. Also, Harikrushna Maharaj is the spotlight of the temple that attracts millions of devotees across the year.</p>
